  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AminoAcid
    Represents the standard amino acids with different categories for cis and trans proline.

    Indicates whether the amino acid can be represented by standard rotamers, is non-rotameric, or contains no rotatable bonds at all.

    A nested enum describing a ProtoAminoAcid as either a C-terminal, N-terminal, or central amino acid
    RamachandranLibrary.Direction
    Indicates whether the amino acid is to the left or to the right of the central one.
